The paper presents a novel stochastic local search algorithm for random binary constraint satisfaction problems (CSP), which is a problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and also involves optimization and search techniques (cs.DS). The algorithm is evaluated on a suite of benchmarks, which involves experimental evaluation and performance analysis (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the limitations and strengths of the proposed algorithm, which involves theoretical analysis and comparison with prior work (cs.CC). Finally, the paper presents new record best solutions for a challenging benchmark instance, which involves data mining and pattern recognition (cs.DM).
